stopgap {
  Stopgap distribution is at https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/manage/publishers/reqlan
}

release_tagging {
  Release automation is tag-driven rather than commit-driven.
  Site deployments are triggered by Git tags matching `site/v*` via ["./distribution.rq".site_distribution].
  VS Code extension publishing is triggered by Azure DevOps tags matching `ext/v*` via ["./distribution.rq".extension_distribution].
}

vsix_export {
  @steps: (
    cd packages/extension
    vsce package --no-dependencies
  )
}

site_distribution {
    GitHub Pages deployment should only run when a developer creates a `site/v*` tag.
    The site workflow should not deploy on ordinary commits.
    The implementation lives in ["../../.github/workflows/deploy-site.yml"].
}

extension_distribution {
    Azure DevOps should build, test, package, and publish the VS Code extension only for tags matching `ext/v*`.
    The tag suffix after `ext/v` becomes the extension package version before publishing.
    The implementation lives in ["../../azure-pipelines.yml"].
    VSIX packaging follows ["./distribution.rq".vsix_export].
}

workflow_deduplication {
    Extension publish automation should have a single authoritative workflow to avoid duplicate marketplace releases.
    Azure DevOps is the authoritative extension publishing workflow per ["./distribution.rq".extension_distribution].
    The site remains deployed by GitHub Actions per ["./distribution.rq".site_distribution].
}
